      job_description:
        'Job Summary\n\nThe Center for Environmental and Regulatory Information Systems (CERIS) is a recognized center at Purdue University which develops custom information solutions that help clients meet workflow and regulatory requirements using knowledge systems that manage, track, and analyze key data. Working in a team and collaborative environment, this position works under general supervision to design, develop, and install new software products or enhancements to existing software. It also includes but is not limited to enhancements to complex data reporting, web-based applications, and mapping applications.\n\nWhat You’ll be Doing\n• Application Development - Develop new and maintain (analyze and modify as necessary) existing applications written in a variety of programming languages. Design, code, test, and debug software. Interpret and document end-user information needs. Maintain system documentation.\n• Meetings – The application developer will participate in regularly scheduled meetings with other team members. These meetings may include other developers, project managers, leadership, and stakeholders.\n• Support - Produce status reports and other technical documentation as required. Occasional creation of PowerPoint presentations and posters, as well as formally presenting at user group meetings.\n\nWhat You Must Have\n• Bachelor’s degree in computer science, computer graphic technology, information systems, or related field\n• Two years of software development experience\n• In lieu of a degree, consideration will be given to an equivalent combination of related education and required work experience (Associates degree with 4 years of experience, High School/GED with 6 years of experience)\n• Systems analysis and programming skills\n• Ability to work independently on time-critical projects\n• Ability to work collaboratively\n• Strong communication skills – written and verbal\n\nWhat We Want You to Know\n• This posting represents two (2) vacancies\n• These positions are a hybrid work schedule\n• All new hires will be expected to follow Protect Purdue guidelines, https://bit.ly/3DH3z6f\n• Learn more about Purdue’s benefits summary, https://bit.ly/3llRBah\n• Purdue will not sponsor employment authorization for this position\n• A background check will be required for employment in this position\n• FLSA: Exempt (Not Eligible For Overtime)\n• Retirement Eligibility: Defined Contribution Waiting Period\n• Purdue University is an EOE/AA employer. All individuals, including minorities, women, individuals with disabilities, and veterans are encouraged to apply\n\nWhat You’ll Get in Return\n\nAll university employees are afforded a generous benefits package, https://www.purdue.edu/hr/benewell/index.php, including medical/dental/vision insurance, paid time off, and retirement contributions. As part of Purdue University’s expansive employee benefit package, the University is proud to offer its employees the opportunity to grow, learn, and advance by offering a tuition remission opportunity at both Purdue University and Purdue Global.\n\nTake Your Next Giant Leap\n\nWe never stop, we keep going, because Discovery is in our DNA, and we want you to discover a Career at Purdue University! Come work alongside a family of diverse culture with faculty, students, and staff who come together to become one, Boilermakers! Our greatest adventures are yet to come, and we want to include you.\n\nCome take your Next Giant Leap and Discover your next career!',
